exif:ImageDescription: Limited use of glans condoms (condoms that only cover the head of the penis) is documented in Asia prior to the 15th century. As was common for birth control at the time, glans condoms seem to only have been used by the upper classes. In China, the may have been made of oiled silk paper, or lamb intestine, but in Japan, they were often made of tortoise shell or animal horn. Ouch.
